trend_summary: Landscape stays chiefly agricultural-forest mosaic. 2000s show more open cropland; later scenes display gradual infill by woodland, merged fields and a small east-central village edging outward. No major infrastructure appears, so built-up cover rises only marginally while green cover increases.
notable_changes: Small residential cluster near the east-central crossroads expands by several blocks.
Several peripheral fields in the northwest and centre revert to deciduous forest.
Field consolidation: hedgerows/plots removed, creating larger rectangular parcels south-centre.
A new farm track or minor road cuts diagonally through mid-sector cropland.
Crop rotation patterns shift, visible as changing seasonal patchwork colours.
